<h2><%= schemaName %> API</h2>

<p>
  <a href="/docs/<%= schemaName %>"><strong>API Documentation</strong></a> | 
  <a href="/docs/<%= schemaName %>/schema">JSON-schema</a>
</p>

<p>See the README file for more futher examples, including how to generate API keys.</p>

<div class="section mdl-color--white mdl-color-text--grey-700 mdl-shadow--4dp">
  <h4>Retrieve schema</h4>
  <p>This does not require an API Key as it is a read only request.</p>
  <p>Returns JSON-schema.</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-900 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">HTTP GET /<%= schemaName %></pre>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl <%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %></pre>
</div>

<div class="section mdl-color--white mdl-color-text--grey-700 mdl-shadow--4dp">
  <h4>Create</h4>
  <p>For create requests an API key must be passed via the <strong>x-api-key</strong> header.</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-900 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">HTTP POST /<%= schemaName %></pre>
  <h5 class="mdl-color-text--grey-600">Example</h5>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl -X POST \
-d '{ "name": "Example <%= schemaName %>", "description": "Description..." }' \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-H "x-api-key: TZX1T-LZTWM-7BW82-89XQT-8A4M2-YQU48" \
<%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %></pre>
</div>

<div class="section mdl-color--white mdl-color-text--grey-700 mdl-shadow--4dp">
  <h4>Retrieve</h4>
  <p>This does not require an API Key as it is a read only request.</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-900 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">HTTP GET /<%= schemaName %>/:id</pre>
  <h5 class="mdl-color-text--grey-600">Example</h5>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl <%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %>/9cb1a2bf7f5e321cf8ef0d15</pre>
  <p>You can also request a JSON-LD response:</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl -H "Accept: application/ld+json" \
<%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %>/9cb1a2bf7f5e321cf8ef0d15</pre>
</div>

<div class="section mdl-color--white mdl-color-text--grey-700 mdl-shadow--4dp">
  <h4>Update</h4>
  <p>For update requests an API key must be passed via the <strong>x-api-key</strong> header.</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-900 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">HTTP PUT /<%= schemaName %>/:id</pre>
  <h5 class="mdl-color-text--grey-600">Example</h5>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl -X PUT \
-d '{ "name": "Example <%= schemaName %>", "description": "Description..." }' \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-H "x-api-key: TZX1T-LZTWM-7BW82-89XQT-8A4M2-YQU48" \
<%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %>/9cb1a2bf7f5e321cf8ef0d15</pre>
</div>

<div class="section mdl-color--white mdl-color-text--grey-700 mdl-shadow--4dp">
  <h4>Delete</h4>
  <p>Removes an entry from the database.</p>
  <p>For delete requests an API key must be passed via the <strong>x-api-key</strong> header.</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-900 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">HTTP DELETE /<%= schemaName %>/:id</pre>
  <h5 class="mdl-color-text--grey-600">Example</h5>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl -X DELETE \
  -H "x-api-key: TZX1T-LZTWM-7BW82-89XQT-8A4M2-YQU48" \
  <%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %>/9cb1a2bf7f5e321cf8ef0d15</pre>
</div>

<div class="section mdl-color--white mdl-color-text--grey-700 mdl-shadow--4dp">
  <h4>Search</h4>
  <p>This does not require an API Key as it is a read only request.</p>
  <p>You can search for text in fields (e.g "?name=foo" or "?description=bar").</p>
  <p>You can also sort by one or more fields in forward or reverse order by passing a 'sort' argument (e.g "?sort=name", "?sort=-name", "?sort=name,description").</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-900 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">HTTP GET /<%= schemaName %>/search?:params</pre>
  <h5 class="mdl-color-text--grey-600">Example</h5>
  <p>Returns all entries with 'foo' in the name sorted by their name:</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl <%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %>?sort=name&amp;name=foo</pre>
  <p>You can also request a JSON-LD response:</p>
  <pre class="mdl-color--grey-800 mdl-color-text--grey-100 mdl-shadow--4dp">curl -H "Accept: application/ld+json" \
<%= baseUri %>/<%= schemaName %>?name=foo</pre>
</div>